  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the reduction of gingival recession of single Miller
      Class I and II defects treated by coronally advanced flap with subepithelial porcine collagen
      matrix graft and / or enamel matrix proteins.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
